{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775821176827,"sessionID":"ses_288d2588effer1XcyOp729BuBT","part":{"id":"prt_d772db47a0015q6klikYpERGq6","messageID":"msg_d772da853001KcAPpX2608FoCb","sessionID":"ses_288d2588effer1XcyOp729BuBT","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_4b691739205c4a18889e5f81","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - find the root directory and key folders\n2. The pkg/workloadmanager module - what files exist there, what's already implemented\n3. Any existing reconciler patterns or K8s controller code in the project\n4. Any existing tasks.md files or planning documents that show the format used\n5. Any ST-3 design documents or specs related to AR-007\n6. The Go module structure (go.mod, imports, dependencies)\n7. Any existing K8s types, APIs, or controller-runtime usage\n8. Test patterns used in the project\n\nSearch broadly - check for directories like \"agentcube\", \"pkg/\", \"docs/\", \"specs/\", \"plans/\", etc. Look for any files mentioning \"reconciler\", \"workloadmanager\", \"AR-007\", \"ST-3\", \"k8s\", \"controller\".\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project root path\n- Full directory tree of pkg/workloadmanager\n- Any existing reconciler/controller code patterns\n- Format of any existing tasks.md or planning docs\n- K8s dependencies and versions used\n- Test framework and patterns\n- Any design docs for ST-3 or AR-007","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_288d23579ffeCqJKrqCu4YiGK5 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Exploration Summary\n\n### 1. Project Root Path\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z\n```\n\n**Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n\n### 2. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\n```\n.sdd_prompt.md\nchanges/            # AR-001 through AR-007 (change request folders)\nci-cd/\ncli-toolkit/\nclient-go/          # Generated Kubernetes client code (clientset, informers, listers)\ncode-execution/\ncoverage.out\ndelta-spec.md\ndeployment/\ndesign.md\ngo.mod\ngo.sum\nidle-cleanup/\nintegrations/\npkg/                # Go packages (apis/, workloadmanager/)\nproject.md\npython-sdk/\nsandbox-orchestration/\nsession-routing/\nsession-store/\ntest_spec.md\ntesting/\n```\n\n### 3. Full Directory Tree of `pkg/workloadmanager`\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── handler/\n│   ├── constants.go          # GVR constants, Kind constants, Label/Annotation constants\n│   ├── models.go             # CreateSandboxRequest, CreateSandboxResponse, SandboxInfo, SandboxStatus, EntryPoint\n│   ├── sandbox_create.go     # SandboxCreateHandler (693 lines) - create + rollback + pod IP resolution\n│   ├── sandbox_delete.go     # SandboxDeleteHandler (216 lines) - delete by session and by name\n│   ├── sandbox_delete_test.go # Unit tests for delete handler + mockStore (387 lines)\n│   ├── sandbox_lifecycle.go  # LifecycleManager (343 lines) - background cleanup, status, list, extend TTL\n│   └── sandbox_lifecycle_test.go # Unit tests for lifecycle manager (696 lines)\n└── response/\n    ├── response.go           # JSON(), Created(), Error(), ErrorWithID() helpers (45 lines)\n    └── response_test.go      # Unit tests for response helpers (110 lines)\n```\n\n**Notable: There is NO `reconciler/` subdirectory yet.** The AR-007 design document specifies it should be created with files like `reconciler.go`, `sync.go`, `agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`, `pod.go`, `event_handlers.go`, `metrics.go`, `types.go`, and corresponding test files.\n\n### 4. Existing Reconciler/Controller Code Patterns\n\n**No reconciler package exists yet in `pkg/workloadmanager/`.** However, there are two related patterns already in the codebase:\n\n#### A. `SandboxReconcilerWatcher` Interface (in `sandbox_create.go`, line 38)\n```go\ntype SandboxReconcilerWatcher interface {\n    WatchSandboxOnce(namespace, name string) (<-chan SandboxStatus, error)\n}\n```\nThis is a **one-shot watcher** interface used by the create handler to wait for sandbox to reach \"running\" status. It is NOT a full reconciler -- it is a simple channel-based notification mechanism.\n\n#### B. `LifecycleManager` (in `sandbox_lifecycle.go`)\nA **polling-based background cleanup loop** (NOT a K8s reconciler):\n- Uses `time.Ticker` with configurable `checkInterval` (default 5 minutes)\n- Lists all sandboxes from Store, checks expiration, deletes expired ones\n- Has `Start(ctx)` / `Stop()` lifecycle methods with `mu sync.Mutex` + `running bool` guard\n- Provides HTTP endpoints: `GetSandboxStatus`, `ListSandboxes`, `ExtendSandboxTTL`\n\n#### C. Reference `SandboxReconciler` in `sandbox-orchestration/design.md` (lines 378-394)\nThe original design doc shows a controller-runtime based reconciler:\n```go\ntype SandboxReconciler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n    watchers map[types.NamespacedName]chan SandboxStatusUpdate\n    mu       sync.RWMutex\n}\n```\nThis uses `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` and is the reference design for what AR-007 will implement, but using the **Informer + Workqueue** pattern instead of controller-runtime's manager.\n\n### 5. Format of Existing tasks.md / Planning Documents\n\nAll change requests follow the same structure under `changes/AR-XXX/`:\n\n**Each AR folder contains:**\n- `proposal.md` -- High-level overview, goals, scope, impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria\n- `design.md` -- Detailed technical design with architecture diagrams, data structures, API contracts, testing strategy\n- `delta-spec.md` -- Normative requirements in Given/When/Then format (BDD-style)\n- `tasks.md` -- Task breakdown with checkboxes and acceptance criteria\n\n**tasks.md format example (from AR-005, which is ST-3/Design Complete):**\n```markdown\n# AR-005 任务清单\n\n> **Stage**: ST-3 (Design Complete)\n> **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n> **Language**: Go\n> **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## T-001: Define GVR Constants\n\n- [ ] T-001.01 Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go`\n- [ ] T-001.02 Define `AgentRuntimeGVR` constant: `schema.GroupVersionResource{...}`\n\n**验收**: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` compiles; GVR values match delta-spec\n\n---\n\n## T-024: Full Verification Gate\n\n- [ ] T-024.01 `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` compiles\n- [ ] T-024.02 `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v` all pass\n- [ ] T-024.03 Line coverage >= 80%\n- [ ] T-024.04 T/C ratio > 0.4\n\n**验收**: All checks pass, AR-005 can be marked complete\n```\n\n**AR-007 tasks.md is currently at ST-1 (Proposal Draft)** with placeholder content -- tasks have not been filled in yet.\n\n### 6. K8s Dependencies and Versions (from go.mod)\n\n```\nGo version: 1.25.0\n\nDirect dependencies:\n  github.com/gin-gonic/gin        v1.10.0    # HTTP framework\n  github.com/google/uuid          v1.6.0     # UUID generation\n  github.com/stretchr/testify     v1.11.1    # Testing framework\n  k8s.io/api                      v0.34.1    # K8s API types\n  k8s.io/apimachinery             v0.34.1    # K8s apimachinery (schema, metav1, etc.)\n  k8s.io/client-go                v0.34.1    # K8s client (dynamic, typed, informers, workqueue)\n  sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime  v0.22.2    # Controller-runtime (used in groupversion_info.go)\n```\n\nKey client-go packages already in use:\n- `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` -- Dynamic client for unstructured CR operations\n- `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` -- Typed clientset for core K8s resources (Pods, Secrets)\n- `k8s.io/client-go/informers` -- Shared informer factory\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` -- `apierrors.IsNotFound()` etc.\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` -- `metav1.Condition`, `metav1.Duration`\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema` -- `schema.GroupVersionResource`\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/labels` -- Label selectors\n\n### 7. K8s Types, APIs, and Controller-Runtime Usage\n\n#### Custom Resource Definitions (CRDs)\n\n**API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n**AgentRuntime** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go`):\n- Spec: `Ports []TargetPort`, `Template *SandboxTemplate`, `SessionTimeout`, `MaxSessionDuration`\n- Status: `Conditions []metav1.Condition`\n- SandboxTemplate embeds `corev1.PodSpec`\n\n**CodeInterpreter** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`):\n- Spec: `Ports`, `Template *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, `SessionTimeout`, `MaxSessionDuration`, `WarmPoolSize *int32`, `AuthMode AuthModeType`\n- Status: `Conditions []metav1.Condition`, `Ready bool`\n- Template: Image, ImagePullPolicy, Environment, Command, Args, Resources, RuntimeClassName, ImagePullSecrets\n\n**GroupVersion info** uses controller-runtime scheme builder:\n```go\nSchemeBuilder = &scheme.Builder{GroupVersion: GroupVersion}\nAddToScheme = SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme\n```\n\n#### Generated client-go Code (`client-go/`)\n\n```\nclient-go/\n├── clientset/\n│   ├── clientset.go        # Interface with RuntimeV1alpha1() accessor\n│   ├── fake.go\n│   └── typed/runtime/v1alpha1/\n│       ├── agentruntime.go       # AgentRuntimeInterface (CRUD + Watch + Patch)\n│       ├── codeinterpreter.go    # CodeInterpreterInterface\n│       ├── runtime_client.go     # RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n│       ├── generated_expansion.go\n│       └── fake/                 # Fake typed clients\n├── informers/externalversions/\n│   ├── factory.go          # SharedInformerFactory (Start, Shutdown, WaitForCacheSync)\n│   ├── generic.go          # GenericInformer, ForResource\n│   ├── runtime/interface.go\n│   ├── runtime/v1alpha1/\n│   │   ├── interface.go    # AgentRuntimes(), CodeInterpreters() accessors\n│   │   ├── agentruntime.go # AgentRuntimeInformer (Informer() + Lister())\n│   │   └── codeinterpreter.go\n│   └── internalinterfaces/ # NewInformerFunc, TweakListOptionsFunc\n└── listers/runtime/v1alpha1/\n    ├── agentruntime.go       # AgentRuntimeLister + AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n    ├── codeinterpreter.go    # CodeInterpreterLister + CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister\n    └── expansion_generated.go\n```\n\n#### External CRDs (consumed, not defined by agentcube)\n- `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1` -- Sandbox\n- `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1` -- SandboxClaim\n\n### 8. Test Framework and Patterns\n\n**Framework:** `github.com/stretchr/testify` (assert, require)\n\n**Test patterns observed:**\n\n1. **Table-driven tests** with `t.Run()` subtests:\n```go\ntestCases := []struct { name string; info *SandboxInfo; now time.Time; expected bool }{...}\nfor _, tc := range testCases {\n    t.Run(tc.name, func(t *testing.T) { ... })\n}\n```\n\n2. **Mock Store interface** -- simple in-memory map-based mock:\n```go\ntype mockStore struct {\n    sandboxes map[string]*SandboxInfo\n}\n// Implements: StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, GetSandbox, DeleteSandbox, ListSandboxes\n```\n\n3. **Gin test context** pattern:\n```go\ngin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)\nw := httptest.NewRecorder()\nc, _ := gin.CreateTestContext(w)\nc.Request = httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodPost, \"/path\", body)\nhandler.Method(c)\nassert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, w.Code)\n```\n\n4. **Fake dynamic client** from `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake`:\n```go\nscheme := runtime.NewScheme()\ndynClient := fake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme)\n```\n\n5. **Constructor tests** verifying nil-safety for optional dependencies\n\n6. **JSON serialization tests** -- marshal/unmarshal round-trip verification\n\n7. **Boundary condition tests** -- exact TTL boundaries, edge cases\n\n**Quality gates:**\n- `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` must compile\n- `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v` all pass\n- Line coverage >= 80%\n- T/C ratio (test code / source code) > 0.4\n- `go test -race` -- no data races\n\n### 9. ST-3 Design Documents and AR-007 Specs\n\n**AR-007 (`changes/AR-007/`)** -- \"K8s Reconciler Controller\"\n\n| File | Status | Content |\n|------|--------|---------|\n| `proposal.md` | Complete | 127 lines -- overview, goals, scope, impact analysis, 4 alternatives evaluated, acceptance criteria |\n| `design.md` | Complete | 549 lines -- full architecture diagram, file structure, data structures (ReconcilerDeps, SandboxReconciler, MetricsRecorder), API contracts, state mapping, workqueue config, event handlers, reconcile logic per resource type, graceful shutdown, error handling, metrics, testing strategy |\n| `delta-spec.md` | Complete | 538 lines -- 16 detailed requirements in Given/When/Then BDD format covering: constructor, workqueue, informer callbacks, cache sync, AgentRuntime OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete, CodeInterpreter, Pod status, key design, state mapping, graceful shutdown, error handling, metrics, handler integration, end-to-end ordering, build/test gates |\n| `tasks.md` | **ST-1 (Placeholder)** | 27 lines -- only header and gate tasks filled in; actual implementation tasks not yet defined |\n\n**Stage progression:** AR-004, AR-005, AR-006 are all at **ST-3 (Design Complete)**. AR-007 is at **ST-1 (Proposal Draft)**.\n\n### 10. Key Design Decisions for AR-007 Reconciler\n\nFrom the design documents, the reconciler will use:\n\n- **Pattern:** Informer + Workqueue (NOT controller-runtime manager)\n- **Workqueue:** `workqueue.NewNamedRateLimitingQueue` with exponential backoff (5s initial, 5min max, 15 retries)\n- **Workers:** Default 2 concurrent goroutines\n- **Cache sync timeout:** 30 seconds\n- **Shutdown timeout:** 30 seconds (using `ShutDownWithDrain` from client-go 0.34+)\n- **State mapping:** CR `Ready` condition --> Store status (pending/running/terminated)\n- **Metrics:** Prometheus counters/histograms (reconcile_total, reconcile_duration_seconds, reconcile_errors_total, workqueue_depth, workqueue_adds_total)\n- **Integration:** Optional reconciler field on handlers for `Enqueue()` calls after create/delete operations\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_288d23579ffeCqJKrqCu4YiGK5","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775820982913,"end":1775821176824}}}}
